---
/**
 * payment-flow.astro вЂ” VerdantForged Stripe lifecycle
 *
 * Documents the four lifecycle paths (happy, failure, insufficient funds,
 * abandoned topup) at a user-visible level. Diagrams are SVG so they render
 * crisp on mobile without depending on an external library.
 *
 * Cross-links:
 *   - ../tee-broker-docs/site/BROKER_RPC.md  (envelope shapes, plan/approve)
 *   - ../tee-broker-deploy/SECURITY_REVIEW.md (data retention, key handling)
 */
import BaseLayout from '~/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import SiteNav    from '~/components/SiteNav.astro';
import Footer     from '~/components/Footer.astro';

// Topup TTL вЂ” the client has this long to add a second PI before the broker
// refunds the original and abandons the job. Aligns with t_<insufficient_funds>.
const TOPUP_TTL_MINUTES = 10;
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Payment flow вЂ” VerdantForged TEE Broker"
  description="How VerdantForged uses Stripe PaymentIntents: verify before execution, capture the actual cost, refund failures, and handle insufficient funds with a topup window."
>
  <SiteNav active="payment-flow" title="Payment flow" />

  <main>
    <!-- в”Ђв”Ђ HERO в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ -->
    <section class="vf-container pt-24 pb-16" aria-labelledby="flow-heading">
      <p class="vf-eyebrow vf-reveal" data-reveal-delay="0">Payment flow</p>
      <h1
        id="flow-heading"
        class="vf-heading-section mt-6 max-w-4xl vf-reveal"
        data-reveal-delay="180"
        style="transition-delay: 180ms;"
      >
        Verify. Run. Capture вЂ” or refund.
      </h1>
      <p class="vf-body-lead mt-8 max-w-2xl vf-reveal" data-reveal-delay="360">
        The broker never takes your money before the sandbox has run. On a
        clean execution we capture the actual cost; on a failure we refund
        the full hold; on an underfunded run we give you a {TOPUP_TTL_MINUTES}-minute
        topup window before we close out.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- в”Ђв”Ђ THE FOUR PATHS в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ -->
    <section class="vf-container section-sm" aria-labelledby="paths-heading">
      <p class="vf-eyebrow">Lifecycle paths</p>
      <h2 id="paths-heading" class="vf-heading-section mt-6 max-w-4xl">
        Four ways a job ends.
      </h2>

      <div class="mt-12 grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-6 max-w-6xl">

        <!-- в•­в”Ђ Path 1: Happy в”Ђв•® -->
        <article class="vf-card" aria-labelledby="path-happy">
          <header class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <span class="vf-eyebrow text-verdigris-deep">Path 1</span>
            <h3 id="path-happy" class="font-display font-semibold text-ink text-body-lg">
              Happy path
            </h3>
          </header>

          <pre class="vf-code mt-6 whitespace-pre overflow-x-auto text-caption leading-relaxed"><span class="cmt"># Requester submits a job with a $0.45 PI hold</span>
client в”Ђв”ЂPOST /v1/jobsв”Ђв”Ђв–¶ broker
broker в”Ђв”Ђverify PIв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв–¶ Stripe <span class="kw">(status=requires_capture, $0.45 held)</span>
broker в”Ђв”Ђattest enclave + run skill
broker в”Ђв”Ђ<span class="str">capture $actual</span> ($0.43)в”Ђв”Ђв–¶ Stripe
stripe в”Ђв”Ђrefund $0.02в”Ђв”Ђв–¶ client <span class="cmt">(auto, partial refund of unused hold)</span>
broker в”Ђв”Ђrelease resultв”Ђв”Ђв–¶ client
client sees: <span class="str">succeeded В· $0.43 captured В· $0.02 refunded</span></pre>

          <p class="mt-6 text-body-sm text-ink-soft">
            Stripe captures only what was actually used. Unused time refunds
            automatically вЂ” no manual request needed.
          </p>
        </article>

        <!-- в•­в”Ђ Path 2: Failure в”Ђв•® -->
        <article class="vf-card" aria-labelledby="path-fail">
          <header class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <span class="vf-eyebrow text-verdigris-deep">Path 2</span>
            <h3 id="path-fail" class="font-display font-semibold text-ink text-body-lg">
              Failure path
            </h3>
          </header>

          <pre class="vf-code mt-6 whitespace-pre overflow-x-auto text-caption leading-relaxed"><span class="cmt"># Job submitted, sandbox starts, skill crashes or enclave fails attestation</span>
client в”Ђв”ЂPOST /v1/jobsв”Ђв”Ђв–¶ broker
broker в”Ђв”Ђverify PIв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв–¶ Stripe <span class="kw">($0.45 held)</span>
broker в”Ђв”Ђattest + run
broker в”Ђв”Ђ<span class="str">run failed</span> (fuel_exceeded / signature_invalid / attestation_mismatch)
broker в”Ђв”Ђ<span class="str">refund $0.45</span>в”Ђв”Ђв–¶ Stripe
stripe в”Ђв”Ђrefund в”Ђв”Ђв–¶ client <span class="cmt">(full, immediate)</span>
broker в”Ђв”Ђrelease error envelopeв”Ђв”Ђв–¶ client
client sees: <span class="str">failed В· $0.45 refunded В· reason in result.err</span></pre>

          <p class="mt-6 text-body-sm text-ink-soft">
            A failed execution costs nothing. The full hold is released back
            to your card as a refund вЂ” usually instant, always whole. For more
            details on payment disputes and chargebacks, see our
            <a href="/terms#dispute-heading" class="vf-link">terms of service</a>.
          </p>
        </article>

        <!-- в•­в”Ђ Path 3: Insufficient funds в”Ђв•® -->
        <article class="vf-card border-copper/40" aria-labelledby="path-short">
          <header class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <span class="vf-eyebrow text-copper-deep">Path 3</span>
            <h3 id="path-short" class="font-display font-semibold text-ink text-body-lg">
              Insufficient funds
            </h3>
          </header>

          <pre class="vf-code mt-6 whitespace-pre overflow-x-auto text-caption leading-relaxed"><span class="cmt"># Original PI covers the lease but tokens ran long</span>
client в”Ђв”ЂPOST /v1/jobs (PI $0.20)в”Ђв”Ђв–¶ broker
broker в”Ђв”Ђverify PIв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв–¶ Stripe <span class="kw">($0.20 held)</span>
broker в”Ђв”Ђattest + run
broker в”Ђв”Ђ<span class="kw">shortfall detected:</span> actual=$0.32, held=$0.20, gap=$0.12
broker в”Ђв”Ђ<span class="str">job в†’ awaiting_topup</span> (held $0.20 NOT captured yet)
broker в”Ђв”ЂPOST /v1/jobs/&#123;id&#125;/topupв”Ђв”Ђв–¶ client <span class="cmt">(amount=$0.12, deadline=+10min)</span>
client в”Ђв”ЂPOST /v1/jobs/&#123;id&#125;/topup (new PI $0.12)в”Ђв”Ђв–¶ broker
broker в”Ђв”Ђverify topup PIв”Ђв”Ђв–¶ Stripe
broker в”Ђв”Ђ<span class="str">capture $0.20 + capture $0.12</span>в”Ђв”Ђв–¶ Stripe
broker в”Ђв”Ђrelease resultв”Ђв”Ђв–¶ client
client sees: <span class="str">succeeded В· $0.32 captured across 2 PIs В· 1 receipt</span></pre>

          <p class="mt-6 text-body-sm text-ink-soft">
            The original hold is paused, not captured. You get a {TOPUP_TTL_MINUTES}-minute
            window to authorise the shortfall. If you don't, we go to Path 4.
          </p>
        </article>

        <!-- в•­в”Ђ Path 4: Abandoned topup в”Ђв•® -->
        <article class="vf-card" aria-labelledby="path-abandon">
          <header class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <span class="vf-eyebrow text-verdigris-deep">Path 4</span>
            <h3 id="path-abandon" class="font-display font-semibold text-ink text-body-lg">
              Abandoned topup
            </h3>
          </header>

          <pre class="vf-code mt-6 whitespace-pre overflow-x-auto text-caption leading-relaxed"><span class="cmt"># Path 3's topup never arrives</span>
job status: <span class="kw">awaiting_topup</span>
broker waits for topup PI...
  вЏ± +{TOPUP_TTL_MINUTES} minutes elapse with no topup
broker в”Ђв”Ђ<span class="str">TTL expiry</span> в”Ђв”Ђв–¶ job в†’ abandoned
broker в”Ђв”Ђ<span class="str">refund $0.20</span>в”Ђв”Ђв–¶ Stripe <span class="cmt">(original hold released)</span>
stripe в”Ђв”Ђrefund в”Ђв”Ђв–¶ client
broker в”Ђв”Ђrelease abort envelopeв”Ђв”Ђв–¶ client
client sees: <span class="str">abandoned В· $0.20 refunded В· topup_window_expired</span>

<span class="cmt"># Result is purged. Worker has already deleted inputs (see security review).</span></pre>

          <p class="mt-6 text-body-sm text-ink-soft">
            No silent double-charges. If you don't authorise the shortfall in
            time, the original PI is released and the job is closed out cleanly.
          </p>
        </article>

      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- в”Ђв”Ђ TIMELINE DIAGRAM в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ -->
    <section class="vf-container section-sm bg-moss/5 rounded-3xl" aria-labelledby="timeline-heading">
      <p class="vf-eyebrow">Timeline</p>
      <h2 id="timeline-heading" class="vf-heading-section mt-6 max-w-4xl">
        The 7 events that matter.
      </h2>
      <p class="vf-body-lead mt-8 max-w-2xl">
        A happy-path job produces this audit trail. Every line is signed by
        the enclave ephemeral key and stored in
        <code class="font-mono text-caption">COST_LEDGER.jsonl</code>.
      </p>

      <ol class="mt-10 max-w-3xl space-y-4 text-body-sm font-mono">
        <li class="flex gap-4">
          <span class="text-copper-deep tabular-nums shrink-0">01</span>
          <span><span class="text-ink">submit</span> вЂ” requester POSTs the job, broker records the PI id</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-4">
          <span class="text-copper-deep tabular-nums shrink-0">02</span>
          <span><span class="text-ink">verify</span> вЂ” Stripe confirms the PI is authable; status <code class="bg-moss/20 px-1 rounded">requires_capture</code></span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-4">
          <span class="text-copper-deep tabular-nums shrink-0">03</span>
          <span><span class="text-ink">attest</span> вЂ” enclave returns SEV-SNP measurement + OpenShell policy hash</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-4">
          <span class="text-copper-deep tabular-nums shrink-0">04</span>
          <span><span class="text-ink">run</span> вЂ” skill executes inside the enclave; tokens accrue per LLM call</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-4">
          <span class="text-copper-deep tabular-nums shrink-0">05</span>
          <span><span class="text-ink">finalize</span> вЂ” broker computes actual cost (lease + tokens)</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-4">
          <span class="text-copper-deep tabular-nums shrink-0">06</span>
          <span><span class="text-ink">capture</span> вЂ” Stripe captures <code class="bg-moss/20 px-1 rounded">$actual</code>; auto-refunds any unused hold</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-4">
          <span class="text-copper-deep tabular-nums shrink-0">07</span>
          <span><span class="text-ink">release</span> вЂ” result envelope (encrypted) + receipt + signed trace go to the requester</span>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <!-- в”Ђв”Ђ WHEN A TOPUP IS NEEDED вЂ” TIMING в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ -->
    <section class="vf-container section-sm" aria-labelledby="timing-heading">
      <p class="vf-eyebrow">Timing</p>
      <h2 id="timing-heading" class="vf-heading-section mt-6 max-w-4xl">
        The topup window.
      </h2>
      <p class="vf-body-lead mt-8 max-w-2xl">
        When the broker detects a shortfall, it pauses capture and posts a
        topup request to the client. The original hold is locked; nothing has
        been charged yet.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-10 max-w-3xl vf-card">
        <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between">
          <span class="vf-eyebrow text-verdigris-deep">awaiting_topup</span>
          <span class="font-mono tabular-nums text-body text-ink">+{TOPUP_TTL_MINUTES}m</span>
        </div>
        <div class="mt-4 h-2 rounded-full bg-moss/20 overflow-hidden">
          <div class="h-full bg-copper" style={`width: 100%; animation: pulse-verdigris 10s linear forwards;`}></div>
        </div>
        <p class="mt-4 text-body-sm text-ink-soft">
          If the client doesn't POST a second PI before the bar runs out,
          the broker refunds the original hold and the job moves to
          <code class="font-mono text-caption">abandoned</code>. The result
          is purged.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- в”Ђв”Ђ CROSS-LINKS в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ -->
    <section class="vf-container section-sm" aria-labelledby="more-heading">
      <p class="vf-eyebrow">Read next</p>
      <h2 id="more-heading" class="vf-heading-section mt-6 max-w-4xl">
        For the protocol-level details.
      </h2>

      <div class="mt-10 grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 max-w-5xl">
        <div class="vf-card">
          <p class="vf-eyebrow text-verdigris-deep">Deep dive</p>
          <p class="font-display font-semibold text-ink mt-3 text-body-lg">
            <a href="/payment/" class="hover:text-copper-deep transition-colors">
              Pillar 04 В· Payment в†’
            </a>
          </p>
          <p class="text-body-sm text-ink-soft mt-4">
            The Stripe lifecycle explained for a non-expert: verify, run, capture or refund,
            and the four paths a job can take. Written for a reader who has used Stripe Checkout
            but is not sure how it composes with hardware attestation.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="vf-card">
          <p class="vf-eyebrow text-verdigris-deep">API contract</p>
          <p class="font-display font-semibold text-ink mt-3 text-body-lg">
            <a href="/docs/" class="hover:text-copper-deep transition-colors">
              Broker RPC envelopes в†’
            </a>
          </p>
          <p class="text-body-sm text-ink-soft mt-4">
            Request/response shapes for <code class="font-mono">/v1/jobs</code>,
            <code class="font-mono">/v1/jobs/&#123;id&#125;</code>, and the
            LLM proxy. Field guarantees, signature coverage, and event
            streams. Live <a href="/docs/" class="vf-link">API reference</a>
            with curl examples.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="vf-card">
          <p class="vf-eyebrow text-verdigris-deep">For agents</p>
          <p class="font-display font-semibold text-ink mt-3 text-body-lg">
            <a href="/agents/" class="hover:text-copper-deep transition-colors">
              Set up &amp; submit a job в†’
            </a>
          </p>
          <p class="text-body-sm text-ink-soft mt-4">
            The end-to-end agent setup: check the broker is alive, register
            a skill, submit a job, poll for the result, decrypt. Copy-pasteable
            curl, exercised against the live broker.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>

<script>
  // Scroll-reveal for sections under the sticky nav
  const observer = new IntersectionObserver((entries) => {
    entries.forEach((entry) => {
      if (entry.isIntersecting) {
        entry.target.classList.add('is-visible');
        observer.unobserve(entry.target);
      }
    });
  }, { rootMargin: '0px 0px -100px 0px', threshold: 0.05 });

  setTimeout(() => {
    document.querySelectorAll('.vf-reveal').forEach((el) => observer.observe(el));
  }, 50);
</script>